19/12/2007
Turkish Prime Minister Recep Tayyip Erdogan sided with Skopje in the name dispute Tuesday.
After meeting with Macedonian counterpart, Nikola Gruevski, he said it is "wrong" to ask a country to change its official name.
(Turkish Daily News, Utrinski Vesnik, Vecer, Zaman, Xinhua - 19/12/07;
AP, Xinhua, Makfax, A1, MIA, - 18/12/07)
